This situation wasn’t very recent and I don’t think it’s very serious, but I still don’t have the answer to what it could have been and I would very much like to know, if you all don’t mind. 

Around late October of 2018 (last year), my muscles began to feel very weak; I even fell over a couple of times when I exerted myself (like running around during gym class- I’m in high school). This never had happened before, granted I’m not very out of shape. However, sometime in very early November while I was walking home from school, I began to feel even more faint than before- at some points it was almost as if I was going to faint, and I even warned the friends I was with of this. When I just touched my own skin it hurt quite a bit for some reason. 

Later that day, at my weekly art class, I began to feel even worse- it became increasingly hard to hold my pencil up because my muscles began to hurt too. My head began to hurt a LOT. When I looked up at the light my eyes really hurt, and I only felt well if I was lying down. At one point I was crying from the pain, and I ended up having to go home early. I was bedridden for almost the entire weekend (it was a Friday), besides forcing myself out of bed to go to my high school’s play. 

Later on in the month it happened again, from which I had to stay home the entirety of the next day from school, but then it never happened again. 


Some info about me from that time: 

Age: 16

Sex: Female

Height: 5’1

Weight: Unsure but I’m estimating about 128-130 pounds at that point

Race: Multiracial (White/Asian)

Duration: About a weekend for the first occurrence, and one and a half days for the second 

Location: Northern New Jersey, USA 

On body: General body muscles, eyes, head, skin (especially on forearms)

Existing medical issues: clinical depression

Current medications: Fluoxetine, 10mg. Consistently taken since February 2018.

Photo: N/A



Thank you!!
